Author: comicsansmasterfont
Text: This sounds like me when my low blood pressure starts to get to me. I’ll feel super “heavy” like you said, like my body is suddenly filled with sand, and moving around feels like I’m swimming through molasses.  It’s weird that it happened while you were eating and drinking caffeine (if low bp is what it was), though. Usually food & caffeine *raise* blood pressure slightly. Bodies are fucking strange though so it’s not impossible.

Author: Pink_salts
Text: This happened to me after I ate a sweet potato. I think it was from the sugar or carbs 🤷‍♀️
